        android:text="Boil the Pork:

In a pot, boil the pork belly, pork ears (if using), and chicken liver until tender. Drain and let them cool.
Chop and Dice:

Once cooled, chop the pork belly, pork ears, and chicken liver into small, uniform pieces.
Sauté Aromatics:

In a pan, heat cooking oil over medium heat. Sauté the minced garlic until golden brown.
Add the chopped onions and cook until they become translucent.
Cook Pork and Liver:

Add the chopped pork belly, pork ears, and chicken liver to the pan. Cook until the meat gets slightly crispy on the edges.
Season:

Pour soy sauce over the meat and stir well. Allow the meat to cook for a few more minutes.
Add minced chili peppers and calamansi juice (or lemon juice). Mix thoroughly.
Add Mayonnaise:

Stir in the mayonnaise. This adds a creamy texture to the sisig.
Adjust Seasoning:

Season with salt and pepper according to your taste preference. Adjust the spice level if needed.
Sizzle:

Transfer the sisig to a sizzling plate if available. If not, a regular plate will do.
Garnish:

Garnish with chopped green onions and red chili (if using).
Serve Hot:

Serve the Pork Sisig hot, with calamansi or lemon wedges on the side."
